cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about dialog system technology and its challenges, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as dialog systems are a subfield of AI and the paper discusses the state-of-the-art technologies for the tasks. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as one of the tasks mentioned is audio visual scene-aware dialog. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the evaluation set-up for each track, which may involve machine learning and training models. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely category but still possible as dialog systems are often used in HCI applications and the paper mentions pragmatic ways of applying end-to-end dialog technologies.
